  "text": "Hence,S andT in (40) are just the approximation of S and T by comparing (36), (42) and (41). Applying Theorem 3.4 in methods (37) and (40), we can conclude that the EulerP method (38) is of mean-square order 1 as well. Note that the midpoint method already preserve quadratic conserved quantity [CITATION_1] , so the projection step is not necessary. Errors in conserved quantity I(x, y) = 1 2 (x 2 + y 2 ) of Euler method and EulerP method are shown in Fig. 4 , from which we find that the projection one preserve the conserved quantity up to the tolerance in the Newton iteration. ",
